location: National Cheng Kung University Fall Orchid Show, Taiwan

measurements.description: Fifteen flowers and 3 buds on one 25-cm tri-branched inflorescence; plant exceptionally grown, 55 cm wide, 29 cm tall, six meticulous shiny dark green leaves, grown in bark in 19-cm diameter, 21-cm tall round pot; sepals and petals light green, darker distally, lateral sepals overlaid purple inferior half basal 2/3rds; lip white, overlaid dark yellow, midlobe overlaid purple; column purple, anther cap white; substance firm; texture matte.
